organizations: National Assn of Stock Car Auto Racing
lead_paragraph: The teenage star Joey Logano raced to his second Nationwide Series victory, holding off his Joe Gibbs Racing teammate Kyle Busch in the Pepsi 300 at Nashville Superspeedway in Gladeville, Tenn. The 18-year-old Logano and Busch ran in the top two and traded the lead for most of the race.
